Introduction

Park ChoA, best known by the mononym Choa, is a South Korean singer and actress under Great M Entertainment. Choa is a former member of the South Korean girl group AOA, along with their sub-group AOA Black, formed by FNC Entertainment.

After Choa's three-year hiatus from the entertainment industry, it was announced that on August 6th, 2020, she recorded a new song for the soundtrack to the drama "To All the Guys Who Loved Me" on KBS2. An entertainment industry official claimed that on August 21st, 2020, Choa signed with Great M Entertainment.
